    "notes": "High-fidelity signals for T1105: (1) executable write to non-standard writable path (ProgramData subdirectory not under a vendor folder) by a non-system process, (2) parent-child chain where the writing process immediately spawns the written file, (3) outbound TLS from a process resident in ProgramData to a non-Microsoft/CDN IP. Differentiate from benign by checking process.executable path against allowlisted installer directories and validating the signing certificate of both parent and child. Correlate EID 3 + EID 11 + EID 1 within a short time window (~5s) from the same PID as a high-confidence composite signal."
